// The byte literal implicit reaches through one level of Opt (task-9
// review, MINOR 5; tests/golden/eval/byte-opt-literal.nv is the accepted
// mirror), but an out-of-range literal is still its own diagnostic, not
// a silent pass-through into byte?'s wider option slot.
fn take(b byte?) bool {
    return b != none
}

fn main() {
    print(take(300))
}
